IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: NORTH SEATTLE COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOUNDATION PROMOTES, SUPPORTS, MAINTAINS, DEVELOPS, AND EXTENDS EDUCATIONAL OFFERINGS AND THE PURSUIT THEREOF AT OR IN CONNECTION WITH NORTH SEATTLE COLLEGE.AMERICAN FINANCIAL SOLUTIONS (AFS) IS A DIVISION OF NORTH SEATTLE COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOUNDATION, THE MISSION OF WHICH IS TO EMPOWER PEOPLE TO IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF THEIR LIVES THROUGH FINANCIAL EDUCATION AND COUNSELING. WE REDIRECT A PORTION OF OUR PROCEEDS TO A FUND THAT PROVIDES STUDENT SCHOLARSHIPS, FACULTY GRANTS, AND OTHER ACADEMIC PROGRAMS FOR NORTH SEATTLE COLLEGE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE NORTH SEATTLE COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOUNDATION (THE FOUNDATION) OPERATES EXCLUSIVELY FOR RELIGIOUS, CHARITABLE, SCIENTIFIC, LITERARY, OR EDUCATIONAL PURPOSES WITHIN THE MEANING OF SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE OF 1954, AS AMENDED. - SEE SCHEDULE O
IRS990.Desc: CONSUMER CREDIT COUNSELING PROGRAM TO ASSIST FINANCIALLY DISTRESSED INDIVIDUALS GAIN CONTROL OF PERSONAL FINANCIAL SITUATIONS THROUGH EDUCATION AND INDIVIDUALLY TAILORED SOLUTIONS. NET REVENUES ARE AVAILABLE AT THE DISCRETION OF THE BOARD TO FUND THE FOUNDATION'S FINANCIAL AND PROGRAMMATIC SUPPORT OF THE COLLEGE.CREDIT COUNSELING - AMERICAN FINANCIAL SOLUTIONS (AFS) HELPS CLIENTS FREE THEMSELVES FROM THE ANXIETY AND STRESS OF CREDIT, DEBT AND FINANCIAL WORRIES BY PROVIDING CREDIT COUNSELING, FINANCIAL EDUCATION AND DEBT MANAGEMENT SERVICES THAT PUT CLIENTS IN CONTROL OF THEIR FINANCIAL SUCCESS. 8,974 CLIENTS WERE COUNSELED IN A CONFIDENTIAL, ONE-ON-ONE COUNSELING SESSION, WHERE CERTIFIED CREDIT COUNSELORS HELP ASSESS CLIENTS' SITUATIONS AND IDENTIFY OPTIONS TO MANAGE AND PAY OFF DEBTS. THERE IS NO CHARGE FOR COUNSELING OR EDUCATION SERVICES. DEBT MANAGEMENT PLANS - ONE OF THE OPTIONS AVAILABLE TO CLIENTS WHO ARE STRUGGLING WITH REPAYING UNSECURED DEBT IS A DEBT MANAGEMENT PLAN. A DEBT MANAGEMENT PLAN IS A WAY TO CONSOLIDATE CREDIT AND UNSECURED DEBT INTO ONE MONTHLY PAYMENT THAT FITS WITHIN A CLIENT'S BUDGET, ALLOWING REPAYMENT OF DEBTS MORE QUICKLY OVER TIME THAN WOULD OTHERWISE BE POSSIBLE. CHARGES APPLY TO ENROLL IN DEBT MANAGEMENT PLANS BUT FEES ARE WAIVED IN CASES OF FINANCIAL HARDSHIP. THESE FEES ARE REGULATED BY THE 50 STATES IN WHICH AFS IS LICENSED AND BY INDUSTRY GUIDELINES DEVELOPED BY NON-PROFIT CREDIT COUNSELING AGENCIES. 4,546 DEBT MANAGEMENT PLANS WERE ENTERED INTO DURING THE FISCAL YEAR.HOME FORECLOSURE COUNSELING - AFS IS A SUB-GRANTEE OF THE WASHINGTON STATE HOUSING FINANCE COMMISSION, A HUD-APPROVED HOUSING COUNSELING AGENCY. AFS OFFERS ASSISTANCE TO CLIENTS TO HELP THEM TRY TO AVOID THE LOSS OF THEIR HOMES. IN CONFIDENTIAL, ONE-ON-ONE COUNSELING SESSIONS, 168 CLIENTS WERE OFFERED HELP BY AFS COUNSELORS WHO ASSESS THEIR SITUATIONS, INFORM THEM OF OPTIONS AND WORK DIRECTLY WITH THEIR LENDERS TO TRY TO FIND SOLUTIONS THAT WILL WORK FOR THE CLIENT. MORTGAGE COUNSELING SESSIONS ARE OFFERED FREE OF CHARGE TO CLIENTS.HOME BUYER COUNSELING - AFS ASSISTS CLIENTS TO PREPARE FOR HOME OWNERSHIP BY ASSESSING THEIR INCOME, ASSETS, MONTHLY EXPENSES AND DEBT. OUR COUNSELORS HELP CLIENTS UNDERSTAND THE LENDING PROCESS AND DETERMINE WHAT THEY CAN BORROW, ESTABLISH GOALS FOR SAVING FOR A DOWN PAYMENT AND INFORM THEM OF DOWN PAYMENT ASSISTANCE PROGRAMS IN THE LOCAL COMMUNITY. OUR HOUSING COUNSELORS WILL ASSIST WITH PREPARATION OF A HOME BUDGET INCLUDING EXPENSES RELATED TO THE HOME SUCH AS UTILITIES, MAINTENANCE, TAXES AND INSURANCE. THE COUNSELORS ALSO OFFER TO REVIEW LOAN DOCUMENTS TO ENSURE THAT THE CLIENT UNDERSTANDS THEM. 12 CLIENTS RECEIVED HOMEBUYER COUNSELING DURING THE FISCAL YEAR.COUNSELING BEFORE BANKRUPTCY - IN CONFIDENTIAL, ONE-ON-ONE COUNSELING SESSIONS, AFS CERTIFIED CREDIT COUNSELORS HELPED 180 CLIENTS ASSESS THEIR CURRENT INCOME AND ASSETS VERSUS MONTHLY EXPENSES AND DEBTS. WITH THIS INFORMATION, AFS CREATES AN ACCURATE AND DETAILED MONTHLY BUDGET THAT CAPTURES THE CLIENT'S OVERALL FINANCIAL SITUATION. THIS PROCESS ALLOWS THE COUNSELOR TO BETTER EXPLAIN WHAT BANKRUPTCY MEANS TO THE CLIENT AND THE POSSIBLE ALTERNATIVES FOR HANDLING DEBTS. AFS IS APPROVED BY THE EXECUTIVE OFFICE FOR U.S. TRUSTEES (EOUST) TO ISSUE CERTIFICATES OF CREDIT COUNSELING IN COMPLIANCE WITH THE BANKRUPTCY CODES OF ALASKA, ARIZONA, ARKANSAS, CALIFORNIA, COLORADO, CONNECTICUT, DELAWARE, FLORIDA, GEORGIA, HAWAII, IDAHO, ILLINOIS, INDIANA, IOWA, KANSAS, KENTUCKY, LOUISIANA, MAINE, MARYLAND, MASSACHUSETTS, MICHIGAN, MINNESOTA, MISSISSIPPI, MISSOURI, MONTANA, NEBRASKA, NEW HAMPSHIRE, NEW MEXICO, NEVADA, NEW JERSEY, NEW YORK, NORTH DAKOTA, OHIO, OKLAHOMA, OREGON, PENNSYLVANIA, RHODE ISLAND, SOUTH CAROLINA, SOUTH DAKOTA, TENNESSEE, TEXAS, UTAH, VERMONT, VIRGINIA, WASHINGTON, WEST VIRGINIA, WYOMING, WASHINGTON DC, AND WISCONSIN. APPROVAL DOES NOT ENDORSE OR ASSURE THE QUALITY OF AN AGENCY'S SERVICES.POST-BANKRUPTCY EDUCATION - THE BANKRUPTCY CODE REQUIRES CONSUMERS TO COMPLETE AN APPROVED FINANCIAL EDUCATION COURSE, ALSO KNOWN AS POST-BANKRUPTCY CREDIT COUNSELING, WITH AN APPROVED AGENCY BEFORE DEBTS CAN BE DISCHARGED. AFS PROVIDES THIS COURSE UTILIZING THE "MONEY IN MOTION" PROGRAM. AFS IS APPROVED BY THE EXECUTIVE OFFICE FOR U.S. TRUSTEES (EOUST) TO PROVIDE THE REQUIRED POST-BANKRUPTCY EDUCATION IN COMPLIANCE WITH THE BANKRUPTCY CODES OF ALASKA, ARIZONA, ARKANSAS, CALIFORNIA, COLORADO, CONNECTICUT, DELAWARE, FLORIDA, GEORGIA, HAWAII, IDAHO, ILLINOIS, INDIANA, IOWA, KANSAS, KENTUCKY, LOUISIANA, MAINE, MARYLAND, MASSACHUSETTS, MICHIGAN, MINNESOTA, MISSISSIPPI, MISSOURI, MONTANA, NEBRASKA, NEVADA, NEW HAMPSHIRE, NEW JERSEY, NEW MEXICO, NEW YORK, NORTH DAKOTA, OHIO, OKLAHOMA, OREGON, PENNSYLVANIA, RHODE ISLAND, SOUTH CAROLINA, SOUTH DAKOTA, TENNESSEE, TEXAS, UTAH, VERMONT, VIRGINIA, WASHINGTON, WEST VIRGINIA, WISCONSIN, WYOMING, AND WASHINGTON DC. THERE WERE 174 CLIENTS SERVED DURING THE YEAR.STUDENT LOAN COUNSELING - AFS CERTIFIED STUDENT LOAN COUNSELORS HELP PERSONS MANAGE THEIR STUDENT LOANS WITH A PLAN SPECIFICALLY TAILORED TO THEM. THE PROGRAM IS DESIGNED TO HELP CLIENTS SUCCESSFULLY MANAGE THEIR STUDENT LOAN DEBT AND AVOID THE NEGATIVE CONSEQUENCES OF LOAN DELINQUENCY AND DEFAULT. COUNSELORS HELP EVALUATE LOAN INFORMATION, REVIEW AVAILABLE PAYMENT OPTIONS AND PUT A PLAN IN PLACE FOR REPAYMENT. WE ASSISTED 147 PEOPLE WITH THEIR STUDENT LOANS DURING THIS TIME. ADDITIONALLY, AFS OFFERS RESOURCES THAT SUPPORT BUSINESSES AND ORGANIZATIONS WORKING WITH EMPLOYEES WHO HAVE STUDENT LOANS. WE PROVIDE EMPLOYERS AND EMPLOYEES ONSITE CLASSES, WORKBOOKS AND ONE-ONE-ONE COUNSELING.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: SUPPORTS NORTH SEATTLE COLLEGE THROUGH FINANCIAL CONTRIBUTIONS FOR SCHOLARSHIPS, FACULTY GRANTS AND OTHER PURPOSES, AND BY PROVIDING FOUNDATION PERSONNEL THE RESOURCES FOR SPECIFIC EDUCATIONAL PROJECTS IN COLLABORATION WITH THE COLLEGE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: PUBLIC EDUCATIONAL OUTREACH ACTIVITIES FOCUS ON CONSUMER DEBT AND OTHER PERSONAL FINANCE SUBJECTS, INCLUDING FREE WORKSHOPS, SEMINARS, PUBLICATIONS AND ONLINE COURSES. 5,253 INDIVIDUALS PARTICIPATED IN FACE TO FACE AND ONLINE EDUCATION CLASSES.FINANCIAL LITERACY EDUCATION - AFS HAS A 10-PART CURRICULUM AVAILABLE, FOR FREE, ON OUR WEBSITE OR VIA WORKBOOK. THE COURSES COVER BUDGETING, BORROWING, INVESTING, BANKING, PAYING FOR COLLEGE, STUDENT LOAN REPAYMENT AND INCLUDE A SPECIAL COURSE GEARED FOR YOUNG ADULTS AGED 18 TO 24. AFS ALSO CONDUCTS IN PERSON WORKSHOPS IN WESTERN WASHINGTON. THESE WORKSHOPS HELP TO BUILD THE KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS AND BEHAVIORS NECESSARY FOR PEOPLE TO SUCCESSFULLY MANAGE THEIR FINANCES. A VARIETY OF PROGRAMS ARE AVAILABLE FOR ADULTS, YOUNG ADULTS, PARENTS AND TEACHERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AMERICAN FINANCIAL SOLUTIONS, A DIVISION OF NORTH SEATTLE COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOUNDATION, COLLECTS PAYMENTS FROM CLIENTS THAT IT DISTRIBUTES TO VARIOUS CREDITORS ON THE CLIENT'S BEHALF IN ACCORDANCE WITH EACH CLIENT'S DEBT MANAGEMENT PLAN. THE AMOUNTS COLLECTED BUT NOT YET REMITTED TO CREDITORS ARE SHOWN AS CASH HELD IN TRUST WITH A CORRESPONDING LIABILITY FOR THE AMOUNTS HELD IN TRUST.
NORTH SEATTLE COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOUNDATION GRANTED FUNDS FOR SCHOLARSHIPS, FACULTY GRANTS AND OTHER PURPOSES. A SUMMARY IS RECEIVED FROM THE RECIPIENTS SHOWING HOW THE FUNDS WERE SPENT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART I, LINE 6 - VOLUNTEER ACTIVITIES:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THERE WERE TWO VOLUNTEERS DURING THE YEAR. THE VOLUNTEERS SERVED ON THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, ONE AS AN EX-OFFICIO BOARD MEMBER AND ONE WHO SERVED WITHOUT ACCEPTING A MEETING FEE. THE ADDITIONAL SEVEN VOTING DIRECTORS OF THE BOARD CONTRIBUTED A SIGNIFICANT AMOUNT OF TIME TO THE ORGANIZATION. HOWEVER, THEY RECEIVED A NOMINAL MEETING FEE FOR THEIR SERVICE AND ARE THEREFORE NOT INCLUDED ON PART I, LINE 6 OF THE TAX RETURN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART III, LINE 1, ORGANIZATION MISSION STATEMENT
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: INCLUDING PROMOTING, SUPPORTING, MAINTAINING, DEVELOPING, AND EXTENDING EDUCATIONAL OFFERINGS AND THE PURSUIT THEREOF AT OR IN CONNECTION WITH NORTH SEATTLE COLLEGE. AMERICAN FINANCIAL SOLUTIONS (AFS) IS A DIVISION OF NORTH SEATTLE COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOUNDATION, A NON-PROFIT 501(C)(3) TAX EXEMPT ORGANIZATION. AFS IS DEDICATED TO: -EDUCATING THE PUBLIC ON THE PROPER USE OF CREDIT, DEBT MANAGEMENT, AND OTHER RELATED PURPOSES. -PROVIDING FINANCIAL SUPPORT TO NORTH SEATTLE COLLEGE TO FUND STUDENT SCHOLARSHIPS AND OTHER EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS. NO PART OF THE NET EARNINGS OF THE FOUNDATION OR OF AFS INURES TO THE BENEFIT OF ANY PRIVATE PERSON OR ORGANIZATION OTHER THAN STUDENT SCHOLARSHIPS AND RELATED PROGRAMS OF NORTH SEATTLE COLLEGE. AFS WAS ESTABLISHED AS A PROGRAM OF THE FOUNDATION DURING THE FISCAL YEAR ENDED JUNE 30, 1999. AFS OPERATES A CONSUMER CREDIT COUNSELING PROGRAM AND AS SUCH, OFFERS COUNSELING, EDUCATION, REFERRAL RESOURCES, AND DEBT MANAGEMENT PROGRAMS TO ITS CALLERS. AFS ALSO OFFERS A VARIETY OF EDUCATIONAL AND COUNSELING RESOURCES AND PROGRAMS TO THE GENERAL PUBLIC AND COMMUNITY ORGANIZATIONS. THE PURPOSE OF THESE SERVICES IS TO ENABLE FINANCIALLY DISTRESSED PEOPLE TO HAVE A BETTER UNDERSTANDING OF THEIR PERSONAL FINANCES AND USE OF CREDIT BY OFFERING RESOURCES AND ALTERNATIVES TO THEM. PROGRAMS OFFERED INCLUDE FINANCIAL LITERACY EDUCATION, CREDIT COUNSELING, DEBT MANAGEMENT PLANS, HOME FORECLOSURE COUNSELING, COUNSELING BEFORE BANKRUPTCY, POST-BANKRUPTCY EDUCATION AND STUDENT LOAN COUNSELING.
NORTH SEATTLE COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOUNDATION INTENDS TO FILE FORM 990-T AFTER FILING FORM 990, BUT BEFORE THE FINAL DUE DATE FOR FILING THE RETURN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH BOARD MEMBER IS PROVIDED A COPY OF THE FORM 990 AND ASKED TO REVIEW THE FORM AND PROVIDE ANY COMMENTS PRIOR TO FILING WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS COMPLETE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST DISCLOSURE YEARLY. THE INFORMATION IS REVIEWED TO ENSURE THERE ARE NO CONFLICTS. IF A CONFLICT OF INTEREST ARISES WITH A BOARD MEMBER, THEY WILL NOT BE ABLE TO PARTICIPATE IN DISCUSSION OR VOTE ON SUCH TRANSACTION OR ARRANGEMENT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVIEWS AND SETS THE SALARY OF THE CEO BASED UPON COMPARABILITY DATA. IN ADDITION, THEY APPROVE THE SALARIES SUGGESTED BY THE CEO FOR HER DIRECT REPORTS. SALARY REVISIONS WERE BASED ON LOCAL SALARY SURVEYS OBTAINED AND JOB PERFORMANCE. THE COMPENSATION REVIEW WAS PERFORMED IN AUGUST OF 2017.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION WOULD REVIEW EACH REQUEST AND IF DEEMED REASONABLE, PROVIDE COPIES OF THE REQUESTED DATA.

THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE HAS ESTABLISHED GUIDELINES FOR TAX EXEMPT CREDIT COUNSELING ORGANIZATIONS, WHICH ARE DESCRIBED IN IRC SECTION 501(Q). NORTH SEATTLE COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOUNDATION REVIEWS THESE GUIDELINES EACH YEAR AND VERIFIES THAT IT DOES MEET THE REQUIREMENTS OF IRC SECTION 501(Q), AS FOLLOWS: THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES CREDIT COUNSELING SERVICES TAILORED TO THE SPECIFIC NEEDS AND CIRCUMSTANCES OF THE CONSUMER; DOES NOT MAKE LOANS TO DEBTORS; PROVIDES ONLY INCIDENTAL SERVICES TO IMPROVE CONSUMER CREDIT RECORDS AND CREDIT HISTORY, AND DOES NOT CHARGE A SEPARATE FEE FOR SUCH SERVICES; DOES NOT REFUSE SERVICES BASED ON ABILITY TO PAY OR INELIGIBILITY/UNWILLINGNESS OF CONSUMER TO ENROLL IN A DEBT MANAGEMENT PLAN (DMP); CHARGES REASONABLE FEES AND PROVIDES WAIVERS IF CONSUMER IS UNABLE TO PAY; THE MAJORITY OF THE ORGANIZATION'S BOARD MEMBERS REPRESENT BROAD INTERESTS OF THE PUBLIC AND ARE NOT EMPLOYED BY THE ORGANIZATION OR BENEFIT FROM IT; THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT HAVE OWNERSHIP IN AN ENTITY THAT IS INVOLVED IN THE CREDIT COUNSELING OR SIMILAR BUSINESS; AND DOES NOT PAY FOR REFERRALS OR RECEIVE AMOUNTS FOR PROVIDING REFERRALS FOR DEBT MANAGEMENT PLANS. IN ADDITION, THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT SOLICIT CONTRIBUTIONS FROM CONSUMERS DURING THE INITIAL COUNSELING PROCESS, OR WHILE A CONSUMER IS RECEIVING SERVICES FROM THE ORGANIZATION; AND THE AMOUNT OF REVENUE THE ORGANIZATION RECEIVES FROM ITS CUSTOMERS' CREDITORS ATTRIBUTABLE TO DMP SERVICES DOES NOT EXCEED THE LIMIT OF 50 PERCENT OF TOTAL REVENUES.
